AUTOZOOIDS. Rhomboidal to hexagonal, longer than wide (mean L/W = 1.21). Frontal shield relatiVely flat to moderately conVex, entirely coVered by distinct nodules of Varying shape with 30–35 pseudopores (diameter 
5–15 µm
) intercalated between them, plus 5–10 round marginal areolar pores, larger than frontal pores (diameter 
20–45 µm
); except for a single areolar pore distal to aVicularium rostrum, area between proximal margin of the orifice and ascopore field and directly proximally to aVicularium rostrum usually devoid of pores.

PRIMARY ORIfICE. Transversely D-shaped with a straight, distinctly crenulated hingeline; in each corner a short, blunt denticle directed distally; distolateral orificial rim with numerous low rounded and irregularly distributed denticles of variable size; operculum smooth but with a broad and slightly bent transverse depression in the centre; three or four distal oral spines (diameter 
15–20 µm
); no peristome.
